TITLE: Fintech firm Klarna halves net loss in first quarter as it races toward profitability
SUMMARY: The results show that Klarna is making "significant strides" toward profitability on a monthly basis by the second half of 2023, the firm said.

TITLE: Gap shares soar after retailer reports big improvement in margins
SUMMARY: Apparel retailer Gap reported another quarter of net losses and sale dips across its four brands but did manage to significantly improve its margins.

TITLE: Best Buy shares rise on earnings beat, even as CEO says shoppers are showing 'recessionary behaviors'
SUMMARY: Best Buy shares rose, but the retailer expects weaker spending on consumer electronics the rest of the year.

TITLE: Nvidia shares spike 26% on huge forecast beat driven by A.I. chip demand
SUMMARY: Nvidia is the top provider of advanced GPU chips for artificial intelligence.

SUMMARY: Snowflake beat on the top and bottom lines for the fiscal first quarter, but it gave product revenue guidance that missed consensus estimates.

TITLE: American Eagle Outfitters shares sink as retailer lowers forecast
SUMMARY: The mall-based retailer's results diverged from Abercrombie & Fitch's earlier in the day.

TITLE: Abercrombie & Fitch surges more than 30% after reporting surprise profit
SUMMARY: Mall apparel retailer Abercrombie & Fitch surprised investors with a fiscal first-quarter profit, sending shares surging.

TITLE: Chinese Tesla rival shares dive 11% after it forecasts a plunge in car deliveries
SUMMARY: Xpeng has been hurt by a tough macroeconomic situation in China as well as rising competition from Tesla, BYD and electric car startups.

TITLE: Kohl's shares jump as retailer reports a surprise profit
SUMMARY: Kohl's unexpectedly posted a profit and reaffirmed its full-year guidance.

TITLE: Shares of Urban Outfitters spike after fiscal first-quarter earnings beat
SUMMARY: Shares of Urban Outfitters spiked about 8% after the company reported fiscal first-quarter earnings that beat on the top and bottom lines.

TITLE: Lowe's cuts full-year sales forecast, even as it tops earnings and revenue estimates
SUMMARY: Lowe's beat first-quarter earnings expectations but lowered its full-year sales outlook.

SUMMARY: Ryanair CEO Michael O'Leary said the airline's "industry leading" fuel hedging contributed significantly to its full-year profit.

TITLE: Foot Locker's 27% plunge, guidance cut may signal trouble ahead for other retailers
SUMMARY: Foot Locker shares plunged more than 27% on Friday after a slowdown in consumer spending led to a drop in sales and weak guidance.

TITLE: Bath & Body Works' stock surges after it raises guidance, beats on earnings
SUMMARY: Bath & Body Works saw year-over-year declines in sales and profits in its fiscal first quarter, but its stock surged after it raised its guidance for the year.

TITLE: Alibaba plans to list cloud division as quarterly revenue misses expectations
SUMMARY: Alibaba announced plans to spin off its cloud division as a separate, publicly-traded company. The e-commerce titan's quarterly revenues missed expectations.

TITLE: Walmart raises full-year guidance, as earnings beat on boost from grocery and online businesses
SUMMARY: The discounter's report comes after Home Depot and Target posted weaker sales trends.

TITLE: Target tops earnings expectations, even as sales barely budge and consumers watch spending
SUMMARY: Target's comparable sales were flat as consumers bought more necessities, and the retailer said it expects more sluggishness in the current quarter.

TITLE: Tencent posts fastest jump in quarterly revenue in more than a year after China reopens
SUMMARY: Tencent reported its fastest quarterly revenue growth in more than a year as the company saw a big rebound in payment volumes, ad sales, and gaming.

TITLE: Home Depot posts worst revenue miss in about 20 years, lowers forecast as consumers delay big projects
SUMMARY: The home improvement retailer said customers are taking on smaller projects and skipping big-ticket purchases, such as patio sets and grills.

TITLE: Vodafone shares drop 7% after record 11,000 jobs cut as CEO says telco 'must change'
SUMMARY: Vodafone said it would cut 11,000 jobs over three years, out of a total headcount of just over 100,000.

TITLE: Polestar to cut 10% of workforce as delays push upcoming SUV to 2024
SUMMARY: The Swedish EV maker said its net loss narrowed dramatically compared with a year ago.

TITLE: Disney’s streaming losses improve even as subscriber numbers decline
SUMMARY: Disney is also in the process of laying off thousands of employees under CEO Bob Iger's restructuring plan.

TITLE: Shares of Unity pop on revenue beat, rosy forecast
SUMMARY: Shares of Unity pop on revenue beat, rosy forecast

TITLE: Airbnb drops 10% after earnings report offers cautious outlook for second quarter
SUMMARY: Airbnb drops 10% after earnings report offers cautious outlook for the second quarter.

TITLE: Rivian reports a narrower-than-expected quarterly loss, reaffirms EV production target
SUMMARY: Rivian has been working to reduce its spending over the last several months in a bid to conserve cash.

TITLE: Virgin Galactic quarterly loss widens while company preps for spaceflight return
SUMMARY: Virgin Galactic is aiming to fly its first spaceflight in nearly two years later this month.

SUMMARY: Rocket Lab's revenue increased slightly in the first quarter, but losses grew as well, as the spacecraft and launch company added a NASA contract.

TITLE: Twilio stock falls on weaker-than-expected revenue forecast
SUMMARY: Twilio is gaining customers, but some users are opting not to increase their spending because of economic fears.

TITLE: Novavax surges after biotech company unveils job cuts, positive vaccine data
SUMMARY: Novavax still reported bleak first-quarter earnings and revenue that missed Wall Street's estimates.
